abstract: The presidential candidates worked to sell their pitches to the state’s caucusgoers on Sunday, but also ripped into the billionaire they will soon face in the Super Tuesday contests on March 3.
snippet: The presidential candidates worked to sell their pitches to the state’s caucusgoers on Sunday, but also ripped into the billionaire they will soon face in the Super Tuesday contests on March 3.
lead_paragraph: LAS VEGAS — The Democratic presidential candidates raced on Sunday to make the most of their final weekend day before the Nevada caucuses, selling their messages and tearing into their opponents.

abstract: Plus, Bloomberg floods the internet with ads — and the campaign trail with cash.
snippet: Plus, Bloomberg floods the internet with ads — and the campaign trail with cash.
lead_paragraph: I hope your Valentine’s Day was especially good this year. Americans were forecast to break records with their gifting on Friday, spending an average of $196.31 on their loved ones — a 21 percent increase from last year’s average of $161.96, according to the National Retail Federation. Thanks, and you’re welcome, economy! Here’s the rest of the week’s top news in business and tech.

abstract: Her work for the 1965 paperback editions of “The Lord of the Rings” and “The Hobbit” achieved mass-cult status. But she hadn’t read the books when she got the job.
snippet: Her work for the 1965 paperback editions of “The Lord of the Rings” and “The Hobbit” achieved mass-cult status. But she hadn’t read the books when she got the job.
lead_paragraph: Barbara Remington, the illustrator who created the most widely recognized covers for J.R.R. Tolkien’s “The Lord of the Rings” trilogy and “The Hobbit” — which she quickly executed before she even had the chance to read the books — died on Jan. 23 in Susquehanna, Pa. She was 90.

abstract: Joe Biden sharply criticized Bernie Sanders as early voting began before next Saturday’s Nevada Democratic caucuses.
snippet: Joe Biden sharply criticized Bernie Sanders as early voting began before next Saturday’s Nevada Democratic caucuses.
lead_paragraph: LAS VEGAS — Former Vice President Joseph R. Biden Jr. took aim at Senator Bernie Sanders of Vermont on Saturday, calling on him to condemn the “vicious, malicious, misogynistic” rhetoric of some Sanders supporters and to do more to stamp it out.

abstract: Will the Democrats try to replace Donald Trump with a power-hungry plutocrat?
snippet: Will the Democrats try to replace Donald Trump with a power-hungry plutocrat?
lead_paragraph: For a long time the notion of a Michael Bloomberg presidential candidacy seemed like a Manhattan fancy, a conceit with elite appeal but no mass constituency, a fantasy for Acela riders who imagine that the American people are clamoring for a rich person’s idea of centrism.

abstract: New York lawmakers appear poised to bow to the state’s law enforcement lobby and weaken a law that just took effect.
snippet: New York lawmakers appear poised to bow to the state’s law enforcement lobby and weaken a law that just took effect.
lead_paragraph: It just so happens that a campaign to roll back New York’s landmark bail reforms is unfolding as Michael Bloomberg’s presidential run forces a reckoning with stop-and-frisk, the policing tactic that led to the harassment and humiliation of millions of innocent people, most of them black and Hispanic boys and men, while Mr. Bloomberg was mayor of New York City.

abstract: It was brought about by a flawed attempt to use credit markets to broaden access to housing.
snippet: It was brought about by a flawed attempt to use credit markets to broaden access to housing.
lead_paragraph: You would have thought that Michael Bloomberg, the former New York City mayor, had picked the right moment to enter the Democratic presidential primaries. From the rural and heavily white states of Iowa and New Hampshire, the contest now moves to South Carolina, where the Democratic electorate is mostly black. A mayor who three times won the trust of one of the world’s most ethnically diverse cities ought to be on solid ground.
